"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1929244-Equestrian-Team-GB-gold-2024-Paris-Olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"    Team GB have won team eventing gold following a tense morning of showjumping in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 90, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 89, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.802795195136748e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The trio of Tom McEwen, Laura Collett and Ros Canter led France by 4.7 points after the dressage and cross-country phases, despite having their advantage cut when Canter was controversially given 15 jumping penalties in the latter event.\", \"from\": 91, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 103, \"end\": 113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"score\": 0.8873196584612367, \"rank\": 0.07814407814405706, \"text\": \"Tom McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\"}, {\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 148, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9723583915184385, \"rank\": 0.02049422353929086, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the team held their nerve in Ch\\u00e2teau de Versailles as Britain sealed back-to-backOlympicsteam titles for the first time since 1972.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ch\\u00e2teau de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7342895207998745, \"rank\": 0.36185883577031014, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Canter who went first for Team GB, knocking down one fence in her round and avoiding any time penalties to extend the overall lead.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9545010085826258, \"rank\": 0.0476678272170546, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McEwen then produced a clear round under pressure, meaning Team GB had three fences in hand over the French ahead of the final group of jumpers.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4161470950570936e-15, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}, {\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9545010085826258, \"rank\": 0.0476678272170546, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8463212986495277, \"rank\": 0.16917865412263086, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And after Stephane Landois knocked one fence down in the final round for France, and incurred a time penalty, it was Collett charged with sealing gold as she went last overall.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9723583915184385, \"rank\": 0.02049422353929086, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now with four fences in hand, Collett held her nerve to seal glory.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 34-year-old knocked down the last but it mattered little, and she triumphantly punched the air in celebration as her team-mates watched on and embraced.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It confined the French to silver, while Japan took bronze for the country's first ever team equestrian medal at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1172, \"end\": 1178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8463212986495277, \"rank\": 0.16917865412263086, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.7140957608175263, \"rank\": 0.36700455593800396, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9008856091582553, \"rank\": 0.11001884090516566, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgium finished fourth, a place ahead of Switzerland.\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1282, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9875122074085149, \"rank\": 0.012641654690994, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9651175046321001, \"rank\": 0.03583399012996778, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.802795195136748e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels.\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"score\": 0.9357162564455422, \"rank\": 0.0687000378078331, \"text\": \"Amazon Prime\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Collett also remains in contention for individual gold ahead of another showjumping round today.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She now lies third on 23.10 penalty points, behind Christopher Burton of Australia (22.40) and Germany's Michael Jung (21.80).\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Francis_Burton\", \"score\": 0.7574108902496863, \"rank\": 0.23869987355008698, \"text\": \"Burton\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Francis_Burton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Francis_Burton\"}, {\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9784705713533681, \"rank\": 0.020181675781547954, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1809, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.5711489565287039, \"rank\": 0.7034145938874357, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\", \"score\": 0.9988531015029164, \"rank\": 0.0011482035875292052, \"text\": \"Michael Jung\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKewen is also in the running, fourth on 25.80.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The result follows a harrowing build-up for the British team, after Charlotte Dujardin pulled out of the Olympics after a previous video emerged of her excessively whipping a horse.\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1939, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9134967806047766, \"rank\": 0.09412250401431879, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But afterwards Collett admitted she felt \\\"on top of the world\\\" as the team delivered the perfect response.\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have never ever ridden into an atmosphere like that,\\\" she told the BBC, referencing the partisan home support.\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Luckily my horse is one trusty partner and so are my team-mates as well.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We brought it home.\\\"\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2389, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Noah Williams in tears as Tom Daley hugs Team GB partner in emotional interview  Do not miss:Humphries has made passionate Olympics darts plea and put two events on notice  Do not miss:Show your colours and get Team GB's official kit for the Paris Olympics  McKewen added: \\\"She (Collett) jumped amazing.\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2403, \"end\": 2416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"score\": 0.999998273608197, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9545010085826258, \"rank\": 0.0476678272170546, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2614, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9545010085826258, \"rank\": 0.0476678272170546, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was more nervous than her at the end, I much prefer doing it myself.\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a class round from her and to get another gold for Team GB....a first of the games.\\\"\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An emotional Canter, who had appeared to go clear in Saturday's cross-country before being deemed to have hit a flag on the way round, admitted: \\\"I can not really talk.\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hid behind whoever was in front of me at the end there.\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was terrifying.\\\"\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3256, \"end\": 3269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4290626389284587e-20, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3305, \"end\": 3318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4290626389284587e-20, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"